HEADWORD: Accouple
<hw>Ac*cou"ple</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>acopler</ets>, F. <ets>accoupler</ets>. See <er>Couple</er>.]</ety>
<def>To join; to couple.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Englishmen <qex>accoupled</qex> themselves with the
Frenchmen.</q> <rj><qau>Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

